item.title: CVE-2017-8133|2024-08-05T16:27:22.073Z -- huawei%20technologies%20co.%2C%20ltd. -- imanager%20neteco
item.description: Huawei iManager NetEco with software V600R008C00 and V600R008C10 has a command injection vulnerability. An authenticated, remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to send malicious packets to a target device. Successful exploit could enable a low privileged user to execute commands that a high privileged user could execute, causing the files to be tampered with or deleted.
